  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Solving the given equation for <span class=\"italic\">Q</span> gives the quantity of the product sold in terms of <span class=\"italic\">P</span> and <span class=\"italic\">T</span>. Dividing both sides of the given equation by <span class=\"italic\">P</span> yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"T over P, equals Q\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"Q equals, T over P\"></span>. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"Q equals, T over P \"></span> gives the quantity of product sold in terms of <span class=\"italic\">P</span> and <span class=\"italic\">T</span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect and may result from an error when dividing both sides of the given equation by <span class=\"italic\">P.</span> Choice C is incorrect and may result from multiplying, rather than dividing, both sides of the given equation by <span class=\"italic\">P</span>. Choice D is incorrect and may result from subtracting <span class=\"italic\">P</span> from both sides of the equation rather than dividing both sides by <span class=\"italic\">P</span>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
